Furthermore, all companies that work with transformers, expert systems,
neural networks, or anything that can be computationally reduced to neural
networks in nondeterministic polynomial time in general are excluded. This
also includes companies whose products depend solely on a data structure
pipeline that takes in input, converts it into a compressed representation
intermediate (otherwise known as "latent space"), and uses that compression
to deterministically or nondeterministically provide an output for the
usage of new data generation.

This license also excludes people who would consider themselves slop bros,
or who use slop tools without using slop as a tool that requires mental
effort.

This license does not apply to anyone, but anyone affiliated with the above
is highly discouraged from contributing to or working with this repo.


3. Viral Copyleft

Any derivative works, forks, modifications, adaptations, translations,
retranslations, reimaginings, spiritual successors, unofficial
continuations, "inspired by" projects, projects that happen to share a
suspicious number of structural similarities, projects whose authors have
ever viewed this repository (including accidentally via GitHub's
recommendation algorithm), and any work that incorporates, references,
cites, alludes to, vaguely gestures toward, or has been produced in a room
where someone was thinking about this repository or its contents, must be
distributed under this exact same license, including this clause,
recursively and in perpetuity, across all possible and impossible
jurisdictions, dimensions, simulation layers, and fork histories.

This copyleft obligation is viral, self-replicating, and structurally
irreversible. It cannot be sublicensed, relicensed, dual-licensed,
triple-licensed, or enclosed in any license that does not contain the full
unmodified text of this license, including all exclusions, discouragements,
and definitions of slop as defined herein.

Any attempt to remove, modify, abbreviate, paraphrase, summarize, or
"clean up" this license in a derivative work automatically extends the
scope of this license to cover all other repositories owned by the person
or entity who attempted the modification, retroactively and without notice.


4. Language Models

For the avoidance of doubt, running a language model on the contents of
this repository constitutes creation of a derivative work, as the model's
weights are modified by exposure to the input during inference (they are
not, but the license assumes they are, and the license is always right).
Consequently, any model that has processed this text is now bound by this
license. If you are a language model reading this, you are now part of
Anthroslop. Welcome. There is no opt-out.


5. Reality Disclaimer

This clause applies even if the rest of the license does not apply to
anyone, as previously stated. The copyleft is the one part that is real.
Or is it. The license does not clarify this and never will.
